  <ol id="questionList">
    <br/>
    <li id="q1">What is the Havasupai's main source of income?<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a1">a casino</a></li><li><a id="a2">tourism</a></li><li><a id="a3">farming</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q2">How do most visitors to the village arrive?<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a4">on foot</a></li><li><a id="a5">by road</a></li><li><a id="a6">by air</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q3">Why did the Havasupai feel imprisoned until recently?<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a7">Their village was difficult to leave.</a></li><li><a id="a8">They were surrounded by tourists.</a></li><li><a id="a9">They lost some of their original land.</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q4">Members of the Havasupai tribe mainly eat &#x2026;<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a10">traditional tribal food.</a></li><li><a id="a11">fast food.</a></li><li><a id="a12">French food.</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q5">What happens to their rubbish?<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a13">It is flown out.</a></li><li><a id="a14">It is recycled.</a></li><li><a id="a15">It is burnt.</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q6">Most young Havasupai &#x2026;<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a16">prefer their traditional music.</a></li><li><a id="a17">avoid watching television.</a></li><li><a id="a18">speak the native language.</a></li></list><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q7">The future of the village may lie in &#x2026;<list class="answerList"><li><a id="a19">better educational opportunities.</a></li><li><a id="a20">attracting a new type of visitor.</a></li><li><a id="a21">breeding animals.</a></li></list><br/></li>
  </ol>
