<section id="fb1">
  <p align="left">1. The lecturer says 'they live off their visitors', in other words tourists.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb2">
  <p align="left">2. The lecturer says 'to walk' is the only way of reaching the village.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb3">
  <p align="left">3. The lecturer says 'part of their land was incorporated into the Grand Canyon National Park.' so they did lose some of their original land.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb4">
  <p align="left">4. The lecturer says 'the locals prefer hamburgers, hot dogs and French fries' which is all fast food.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb5">
  <p align="left">5. The lecturer says 'all the rubbish has to be removed by helicopter', so it is therefore flown out.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb6">
  <p align="left">6. The lecturer says 'the young Havasupai people still speak their native language'.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb7">
  <p align="left">7. The lecturer talks of having hunters come to the village who will pay large amounts of money to kill animals and that this will 'boost the village economy'.</p>
</section>

